ing relationships with state and federal agencies  the VMI Foundation  and faculty and staff across Post  He has been extensively involved in supporting the Undergraduate Research Initiative and played a key role in organizing the academic program s funding requests and reporting to the Jackson Hope Board of Overseers  Sebastino holds a bachelor s degree in mathematics from The Citadel and a master s of business administration degree from Old Dominion University  Prior to his arrival at VMI  he worked as a licensing associate at Brookhaven National Laboratory  and he is a commissioned officer with more than 21 years of service in both the active and reserve components of the U S  Navy  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 